<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000020#      61.3#">Va. Code Ann. § 20-61.3</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_20-61.3"/><heading><desig>§ 20-61.3.</desig><title>Consequences of a putative father failing to appear</title></heading><bodyText><p>If a putative father fails to appear after having been personally served with notice, in accordance with the provisions of subdivision 1 of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-296"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-296">§ 8.01-296<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          296#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-320"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-320">§ 8.01-320<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          320#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, alleging that he is the father of a minor child, the court shall proceed in hearing the evidence in the case as provided in Chapter 3.1 (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-49.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -49.1">§ 20-49.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#      49.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.) of Title 20 as if the putative father were present. The order of the court in any such proceedings shall be served upon the father in accordance with the provisions of Chapter 8 (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-285"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-285">§ 8.01-285<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          285#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.) or Chapter 9 (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-328"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-328">§ 8.01-328<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          328#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.) of Title 8.01.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1988, cc. 867, 894; <citation normalizedCite="1994 VA CH 869"><content><span normalizedCite="1994 Va. Ch. 869">1994, c. 869<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1994#000869#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PSY0-004G-K0PP-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 20.</desig><title>DOMESTIC RELATIONS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 5.</desig><title>DESERTION AND NONSUPPORT</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification